Reasoning: 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the performance of numerical solvers for solving diffusion equations on HPC systems. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper focuses on the application of computational methods to solve real-world problems in science and engineering. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper discusses the use of scientific libraries (PETSc and TAO) for solving optimization problems. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the parallel implementation of the non-negative computational framework on HPC systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the use of software libraries and performance modeling to optimize the computational performance of the solvers.
